Reasoning: The paper deals with classification of high dimensional data points, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision (cs.LG, cs.CV). The use of hashing and dimensionality reduction also suggests that the paper may fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The application of the proposed method to peptide identification from mass spectrometry data suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
